        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-24T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="41"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d41">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/2463: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-24T00:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 24, 1941—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received June 25—11:13
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>234. Reference is made to my telegram No. 225. Minister for Foreign Relations
                    today stated to me enabling decrees had all been issued. Manager of Bank of
                    Republic informed Commercial Attaché<note n="65" xml:id="d41fn65">Merwin L.
                        Bohan.</note> bank is prepared to purchase platinum for account of Metals
                    Reserve Company charging only necessary expenses of the operation. He desires
                    information regarding price, terms, form of contract with Metals Reserve
                    Company, shipping arrangements, etc.</p>
                <p>Please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
